Docs.summary: Get the host addresses. -or- Set the host addresses.

remarks.para: Property getter documentation:
Get the host addresses.
All host addresses are valid for the resolved service. All addresses share the same port
Property setter documentation:
Set the host addresses.
When registering hosts/services, there can only be one registration including address records for a given hostname.

For example, if a client registers a service with the hostname "MyHost" and the address records of 192.168.1.1 and 192.168.1.2, then other registrations for the hostname "MyHost" must not have any address record, otherwise there will be a conflict.
Portions of this page are modifications based on work created and shared by the Android Open Source Project and used according to terms described in the Creative Commons 2.5 Attribution License.
Get the hostname.

When a service is resolved through NsdManager#resolveService or NsdManager#registerServiceInfoCallback, this returns the hostname of the resolved service. In all other cases, this will be null. The top level domain ".local." is omitted. For example, this returns "MyHost" when the service's hostname is "MyHost.local.".

MemberSignature.Value: public void SetAttribute (string? key, string? value);
.method public hidebysig instance void SetAttribute(string key, string value) cil managed

Docs.summary: Add a service attribute as a key/value pair.

remarks.para: Add a service attribute as a key/value pair.
Service attributes are included as DNS-SD TXT record pairs.
The key must be US-ASCII printable characters, excluding the '=' character. Values may be UTF-8 strings or null. The total length of key + value must be less than 255 bytes.
Keys should be short, ideally no more than 9 characters, and unique per instance of NsdServiceInfo. Calling #setAttribute twice with the same key will overwrite first value.

Docs.summary: Returns subtypes of this service instance. -or- Sets the subtypes to be advertised for this service instance.

remarks.para: Property getter documentation:

Returns subtypes of this service instance.
When this object is returned by the service discovery/browse APIs (etc. NsdManager.DiscoveryListener), the return value may or may not include the subtypes of this service.
Property setter documentation:

Sets the subtypes to be advertised for this service instance.
The elements in subtypes should be the subtype identifiers which have the trailing "._sub" removed. For example, the subtype should be "_printer" for "_printer._sub._http._tcp.local".
Only one subtype will be registered if multiple elements of subtypes have the same case-insensitive value.
